# React Memory Game Project Rules

## Project Context
This is a Memory Card Game built with React + Vite, converted from vanilla JavaScript.
The game uses Pokemon API to fetch card data and implements memory game mechanics.

## Key Files
- docs/conversion-guide.md: Complete conversion guide
- src/App.jsx: Main game component
- src/components/: Individual game components
- src/styles/: CSS modules or styled components

## Coding Standards
- Use functional components with hooks
- Implement proper error handling for API calls
- Use localStorage for best score persistence
- Follow React best practices for state management
- Write clean, readable code with proper comments

## API Integration
- Pokemon API: https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon/
- Fetch 12 random Pokemon per round
- Handle loading states and errors gracefully

## When helping with code:
1. Reference the conversion guide in docs/
2. Suggest React patterns over vanilla JS
3. Include proper error handling
4. Explain the reasoning behind suggestions